{{Quote|I quite like the character, because he's this guardian that has Padmé's ear, and her counsel, and he can say things and decree things that not too many people can get away with as far as her security is involved. Once you get the costume on, it's a regal feeling, because the costume is so restrictive, you're forced to pull yourself up and forced to hold yourself with the shoulders back.|Jay Laga'aia|<ref name="CTS">{{HBCite|47}}</ref>}}
'''Jay Laga'aia''' played [[Captain]] [[Gregar Typho]] in [[Star Wars: Episode II Attack of the Clones|''Attack of the Clones'']] and [[Star Wars: Episode III Revenge of the Sith|''Revenge of the Sith'']].

==Biography==
Because of [[Gregar Typho|Typho's]] [[Eye patch/Legends|eye patch]], Jay Laga'aia often had difficulty hitting his marks on [[Star Wars: Episode II Attack of the Clones|''Attack of the Clones'']] set due to poor depth perception.<ref name="CTS" />

Laga'aia was the Celebrity Host for the Sagamore Ballroom stage at [[Celebration III]] in [[2005]],<ref name="SW.comIII">{{SWArchive|url=community/event/celebration/news20050225.html|text=Jay Laga'aia: Celebrity Host for Celebration III}}</ref> and for the Concourse Ballroom stage at [[Celebration IV]] in [[2007]].<ref name="SW.comIV">{{SWArchive|url=community/event/celebration/news20070302.html|text=Jay Laga'aia: Celebrity Host for Celebration IV}}</ref>

